headline: These Are the Best REITs to Own in 2025, Says KeyBanc
summary: The typical U.S. REIT returned 9% this year, or 13% with dividends, as measured by the MSCI U.S. REIT index.  Next year will look pretty similar for the real estate trusts, according to the 2025 REIT Outlook issued Monday by analysts at KeyBanc Capital Markets.  The average REIT’s total return in 2025 should range from 5% to 15%.
